# BROWSER-post.md - LinkedIn Post Creation, Poll & Repost Patterns

## 🚨 CRITICAL: Shadow DOM

LinkedIn's post/poll/repost creation modal lives inside a **shadow DOM**. All UI elements (buttons, inputs, editors) are INSIDE `#interop-outlet` shadowRoot.

**You MUST query shadow DOM for all post creation interactions:**
```javascript
const host = document.querySelector('#interop-outlet');
const shadow = host.shadowRoot;
// Then: shadow.querySelector(...) or shadow.querySelectorAll(...)
```

Regular `document.querySelector()` will return NOTHING for modal elements. NEVER use it for post creation.

---

## SS 8. Open Post Creation Modal

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `() => {
    var host = document.querySelector('#interop-outlet');
    if (host && host.shadowRoot) {
      var shadow = host.shadowRoot;
      var editor = shadow.querySelector('[contenteditable="true"][role="textbox"]');
      if (editor) return { alreadyOpen: true };
    }
    var startBtn = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('div, button')).find(
      el => el.innerText && el.innerText.trim() === 'Start a post'
    );
    if (!startBtn) return { success: false, reason: 'no-start-post-button' };
    startBtn.click();
    return { success: true };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

Wait 2s after click. Then verify modal opened:

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `() => {
    var host = document.querySelector('#interop-outlet');
    if (!host || !host.shadowRoot) return { open: false, reason: 'no-shadow-root' };
    var shadow = host.shadowRoot;
    var btns = Array.from(shadow.querySelectorAll('button'));
    return {
      open: btns.length > 3,
      buttons: btns.map(b => ({
        text: (b.innerText || '').trim().slice(0, 30),
        label: b.getAttribute('aria-label') || ''
      }))
    };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

## SS 9. Create Poll

### Shadow DOM Selectors

| Element | Selector (inside shadowRoot) |
|---------|-----|
| Poll button | `button` with `aria-label="Create a poll"` (hidden under "More" button) |
| Question textarea | `textarea` with placeholder "E.g., How do you commute to work?" |
| Option 1 | `input#poll-option-1` |
| Option 2 | `input#poll-option-2` |
| Option 3 | `input#poll-option-3` (after clicking "Add option") |
| Option 4 | `input#poll-option-4` (after clicking "Add option" twice) |
| Add option button | `button` with text "Add option" |
| Done button | `button` with text "Done" |
| Post text editor | `.ql-editor[role="textbox"]` or `[contenteditable="true"][role="textbox"]` |
| Post button | `button` with text "Post" (not disabled) |
| Dismiss (verify prompt) | `button` with text "Not now" |

🚨 **Poll option limit: 30 characters max.** The input fields silently truncate typed text to 30 chars, but `nativeSetter` bypasses this truncation. If options exceed 30 chars via nativeSetter, the Done button becomes disabled with no visible error. **Always `.slice(0, 30)` option text before setting.**

🚨 **"Create a poll" is hidden under the "More" button** (`aria-label="More"`) in the post modal. Click More first, then click "Create a poll".

🚨 **"Start a post" button is in the main DOM**, NOT shadow DOM. Click it in the main DOM, then check shadow DOM for the modal. The shadow DOM also contains the messaging overlay — filter it out by checking for editor/Dismiss buttons.

### Step 1: Open modal — click "Start a post" in main DOM, wait 3s

### Step 2: Click "More" then "Create a poll"

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    var host = document.querySelector('#interop-outlet');
    var shadow = host.shadowRoot;
    // Click "More" to reveal poll button
    var moreBtn = Array.from(shadow.querySelectorAll('button')).find(
      b => b.getAttribute('aria-label') === 'More'
    );
    if (!moreBtn) return { success: false, reason: 'no-more-button' };
    moreBtn.click();
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000));
    // Click "Create a poll"
    var pollBtn = Array.from(shadow.querySelectorAll('button')).find(
      b => b.getAttribute('aria-label') === 'Create a poll'
    );
    if (!pollBtn) return { success: false, reason: 'no-poll-button' };
    pollBtn.click();
    return { success: true };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```
