## SS 11. Repost with Commentary

🚨 **Verified 2026-03-26:** LinkedIn removed `/feed/update/` URLs from the feed DOM. Posts no longer have navigable post URLs in search results or the feed. Repost MUST be done **directly from the feed page** — NOT by navigating to a post URL first.

🚨 **Do NOT search for repostable posts** — LinkedIn search returns mostly Pulse articles. Instead, **browse the home feed** (`/feed/`) and pick a relevant post with good engagement.

### Step 0: Browse feed for repostable post

Navigate to `https://www.linkedin.com/feed/`, scroll to find a relevant post. Evaluate the visible text to identify good candidates (author, topic, engagement count). Target: post in our niche (AI, PM, agents) with 20+ reactions from a real person (not a brand/news account).

### Step 1: Click Repost → "Repost with your thoughts" → editor opens (ONE evaluate)

🚨 **Find the correct Repost button** by position — the button must be near the target post in the viewport. Use `getBoundingClientRect().top` to identify which Repost button belongs to which post.

🚨 **"Repost with your thoughts" is a `<div>` in a dropdown**, NOT a `[role="menuitem"]`. Find it by text content match.

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000));
    // Click the Repost button near target post (identify by vertical position)
    var allBtns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button'));
    var repostBtns = allBtns.filter(function(b) {
      return b.innerText.trim() === 'Repost' && b.offsetParent !== null;
    });
    // Target the Repost button at approximate Y position (adjust based on which post)
    var targetBtn = repostBtns.find(function(b) {
      var top = b.getBoundingClientRect().top;
      return top > ${targetMinY} && top < ${targetMaxY};
    });
    if (!targetBtn) return { error: 'no Repost button in range', count: repostBtns.length };
    targetBtn.click();

    // Wait for dropdown
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1500));

    // Click "Repost with your thoughts" (it's a div, not a menuitem)
    var allDivs = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('div'));
    var thoughtsDiv = allDivs.find(function(d) {
      var t = (d.textContent || '').trim();
      return d.offsetParent !== null && t.startsWith('Repost with your thoughts') && t.length < 100;
    });
    if (!thoughtsDiv) return { repostClicked: true, error: 'no thoughts option' };
    thoughtsDiv.click();

    // Wait for editor in shadow DOM
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000));
    var host = document.querySelector('#interop-outlet');
    if (!host || !host.shadowRoot) return { repostClicked: true, thoughtsClicked: true, error: 'no shadow root' };
    var editor = host.shadowRoot.querySelector('.ql-editor');
    return { repostClicked: true, thoughtsClicked: true, editorReady: !!editor };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

### Step 2: Type commentary (shadow DOM `.ql-editor` — set innerHTML + dispatch input)

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    var host = document.querySelector('#interop-outlet');
    if (!host || !host.shadowRoot) return { error: 'no shadow root' };
    var editor = host.shadowRoot.querySelector('.ql-editor');
    if (!editor) return { error: 'no editor' };
    editor.focus();
    editor.innerHTML = '<p>${commentaryText.replace(/'/g, "\\'")}</p>';
    editor.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true }));
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000));
    var postBtn = Array.from(host.shadowRoot.querySelectorAll('button')).find(function(b) {
      return b.innerText.trim() === 'Post' && !b.disabled;
    });
    return { typed: true, postBtnReady: !!postBtn };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

### Step 3: Click "Post" (shadow DOM button)

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    var host = document.querySelector('#interop-outlet');
    var postBtn = Array.from(host.shadowRoot.querySelectorAll('button')).find(function(b) {
      return b.innerText.trim() === 'Post' && !b.disabled;
    });
    if (!postBtn) return { error: 'no Post button' };
    postBtn.click();
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000));
    var editorGone = !host.shadowRoot.querySelector('.ql-editor');
    return { posted: true, editorGone: editorGone };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

